description.narrative: In support of rolling-out Egypt's Education 2.0 Reform, in 2019, UNICEF provided support to strengthen the capacities for delivering quality formal and non-formal learning opportunities for the most vulnerable children. A total of 384,658 children accessed improved and quality teaching and learning environment, including 167,560 children in North Sinai, South Sinai and Ismailia, 60,000 children in poor and rural community schools, 4,513 children with disabilities in inclusive schools, and 60,453 refugee and host community children. Not only, additional 21,645 vulnerable young people were trained on life skills and employability out of which 242 young people established their own small businesses. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:08/12/2019
